    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-10-18T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-10-18T09:00:00-05:00" n="837"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d837">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.414/10–1845: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The United States Political Adviser for Germany</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Murphy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-10-18T16:00:00+02:00"
                            >October 18, 1945—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 4:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>803. Department’s 654, Oct. 11.<note n="94a" xml:id="d837fn94a">See footnote 95,
                            <ref target="#pg_1122">p. 1122</ref>.</note> February 1, 1946 is
                    estimated date for completion of collection of archives and not of exploitation.
                        <pb facs="1132" n="1122" xml:id="pg_1122"/> Department’s instructions as to
                    destruction of low level documents<note n="95" xml:id="d837fn95">Department’s
                        654, which contained instructions on destruction of low level documents, not
                        printed. The telegram stated: “We are concerned about desire to destroy
                        certain so-called low-level documents and records, in particular, papers of
                        the NSDAP and affiliated organizations” and declared that “under no
                        circumstances should such papers be destroyed before examination by State
                        Department representatives.” (840.414/10–545)</note> are being brought to
                    the attention of Director of Intelligence, OMGUS,<note n="96" xml:id="d837fn96"
                        >Office of Military Government of the United States (for Germany).</note> as
                    well as to G–2, United States Forces European Theatre.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Murphy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
